1.0 OFFICE OVERVIEW


The Office of Semantic Territory Administration (OSTA) is a public FRBI filing office responsible for receiving, timestamping, classifying, and routing claims involving mascot custody disputes, hallucinated AI claims, semantic territory conflicts, disputed AI representatives, and model-generated reputation drift.


OSTA exists because the public internet has entered the phase where brands, mascots, public entities, creators, organizations, officials, and companies can be summarized, remixed, misrepresented, hallucinated, drifted, stolen, unofficially represented, or trapped inside semantic territory without clear administrative remedy.


The Office does not physically recover mascots.


The Office does not prosecute dashboards.


The Office does not adjudicate vibes without receipts.


The Office receives the filing, stamps the complaint, opens the docket, and routes the matter to the appropriate desk.


Primary Functions:




Receive public reports of stolen mascots.


Accept hallucinated claim disputes involving AI-generated public profiles.


Document semantic territory conflicts.


Preserve evidence related to unauthorized AI representation.


Route MAIF-adjacent perception integrity complaints.


Maintain public dockets for disputed AI summaries, mascot custody claims, and profile drift incidents.


Issue satirical-but-structured notices when peace was offered multiple times.





