3.0 RELATIONSHIP TO MAIF


OSTA operates as a public filing and intake layer adjacent to MAIF.


FRBI receives the complaint.

OSTA classifies the dispute.

MAIF may audit the perception layer.


MAIF’s role is to inspect how AI systems describe an entity, where models disagree, which claims appear repeatedly, whether the profile has drifted, and whether changes appear organic, stale, hallucinated, or intentionally shaped.


OSTA’s role is to preserve the paperwork when someone says:




“The model made a false claim.”

“Our mascot has been taken into semantic custody.”

“This AI representative is not authorized.”

“This public profile has become haunted.”

“Peace was offered multiple times.”





4.0 ACTIVE FILING TYPES


4.1 Stolen Mascot Report


Used when a mascot, symbolic brand animal, public character, or unofficial representative has allegedly been removed, remixed, abducted, detained, memed, or forced into semantic territory.


Example Filing Title:


SMR-2026-0001-OTTERLY-MASCOT-RECLAMATION



4.2 Hallucinated Claim Dispute


Used when an AI model, public profile, generated summary, or representative system asserts a claim that appears false, stale, weakly sourced, exaggerated, or produced by synthetic raccoon fog.


Example Filing Title:


HCD-2026-0042-PUBLIC-ENTITY-CLAIM-DRIFT



4.3 Semantic Territory Claim


Used when an entity alleges unauthorized symbolic occupation, disputed representational ownership, meme-layer encroachment, or unlicensed presence inside AI-generated semantic space.


Example Filing Title:


STC-2026-0088-MASCOT-BORDER-INCIDENT



4.4 AI Representative Drift Notice


Used when an AI representative, persona, digital twin, public entity profile, or model-generated agent begins speaking outside its expected identity boundary.


Example Filing Title:


ARDN-2026-0188-REPRESENTATIVE-IDENTITY-DRIFT



4.5 MAIF Perception Integrity Referral


Used when the matter requires multi-model review, baseline comparison, drift inspection, claim tracing, or intent-level perception audit.


Example Filing Title:


MPIR-2026-0888-PRE-MANIPULATION-BASELINE-REQUEST



